24/01/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Parliamentary deputy Emiliya Maslarova, an influential member of the Bulgarian Socialist Party, has publicly accused members of the current cabinet of involvement in a cigarette smuggling operation. 
In an interview with a local radio station Monday (24 January), Maslarova said she has evidence to prove that the state-run Blagoevgrad-BT factory conducted illegal cigarette exports. 
She accused deputy prime ministers Lidia Shuleva and Plamen Panayotov, as well as Transport Minister Nikolay Vassilev, of participating in the scheme. 
(Info Radio - 24/01/05)
